note_text:
Patient Name: John Doe
DOB: 04/12/1975
Date of Visit: 03/29/2023

Chief Complaint: Mr. Doe presents with a persistent cough and shortness of breath for the past week.

History of Present Illness: The patient reports that his symptoms started last week and have been gradually worsening. He denies any fever, chills, or chest pain. He reports a history of asthma and allergies.

Past Medical History: Mr. Doe has a past medical history significant for asthma and seasonal allergies. He reports being up to date on his vaccinations.

Physical Examination: The patient is alert and oriented, in no acute distress. His vital signs are stable. Lung auscultation reveals bilateral expiratory wheezing. No other significant findings on physical examination.

Assessment and Plan: The patient's symptoms and history are consistent with an asthma exacerbation. Treatment will include albuterol nebulizer therapy and oral steroids. Follow up in 1 week for re-evaluation.

Signed: Dr. Jane Smith
Date: 03/29/2023

Past Medical History: Mr. Doe has a past medical history significant for asthma and seasonal allergies. He reports being up to date on his vaccinations.

Physical Examination: The patient is alert and oriented, in no acute distress. His vital signs are stable. Lung auscultation reveals bilateral expiratory wheezing. No other significant findings on physical examination.

Assessment and Plan: The patient's symptoms and history are consistent with an asthma exacerbation. Treatment will include albuterol nebulizer therapy and oral steroids. Follow up in 1 week for re-evaluation.
